There seem to be two different implementations of Buffer in a browserifyed package: one coming from Globals and another from Builtins.

The problem is that Buffers created from different codes won't play well together:

as an example:

```
// buff instance created using require
Buffer buff=new require("buffer").Buffer("Hello World"); 
// global reference to Buffer
Buffer.isBuffer(buff); 
// returns FALSE which is wrong.
```

Buffer.isBuffer(x) is a pattern used all across streams to allow them to take either an String or a Buffer.

isBuffer(x) relies on checking which constructor created the instance. Even if the globals /builtin are exactly the same version, this method won't work.

