Is there any supported way for code run through browserify to get access to Node's require? I want to inline specific files without breaking the ability to require others using NodeJS.

I'm running an experiment with a project that currently runs in NodeJS and the browser using this method:

```
if (typeof exports !== "undefined" && exports !== null) {
  MyProject = exports;
  ExternalDependency = require('external-dependency');
} else {
  this.MyProject = {};
  ExternalDependency = this.ExternalDependency
}
```

When I run this through browserify I can use `-i` to ignore my `external-dependency`, but then it becomes an empty object.

As an extremely hacky work-around I tried prefixing the output file with:

```
realRequire = require;
```

and then changing

```
ExternalDependency = realRequire('external-dependency');
```

Using that hack I'm able to run the file in NodeJS (browser is untested)

